By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – President Muhammadu Buhari is currently in a crucial meeting with security chiefs at the State House. The security council is made up of heads of security agencies in the country. Some of those present include the Chief of Defence Staff, Gen. Gabriel Olonisakin; the Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai; Chief of Naval Staff, Rear Admiral Ibok Ekwe-Ibas; and Chief of Air Staff, Air Marshal Abubakar Sadique. Others are the Inspector General of Police (IG), Mohammed Adamu; Director-General of Department of State Services (DSS), Yusuf Bichi; and Director-General of the National Intelligence Agency (NIA), Ahmed Rufai. The agenda of the meeting is yet to be confirmed. Sundiata Post recalls that the meeting is coming few days after the apex socio-cultural group In the north, Arewa Consultative Forum (ACF) urged the Federal Government to restrategise and deploy technological method in the fight against insecurity in the country. Details later….